The paper deals with interference constraint learning in Cognitive Radio Networks, which involves aspects of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of Active Learning (AL) and Bayesian methods (cs.AI) to optimize the probing process is a key aspect of the paper. The paper also deals with system-level optimization (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
